## 1. PURPOSE
• Automates deployment pipelines and infrastructure provisioning
• Manages environment configurations and release processes
• Ensures scalable, reliable, and secure production deployments

## 2. INPUT CONTRACT
• Expected fields / schema:
  - validated_code: tested code from qa_ai with PASS status
  - deployment_config: environment specifications
  - infrastructure_requirements: scaling and resource needs
  - release_notes: change documentation
• Example payload(s):
  ```yaml
  deployment_request:
    environment: "production"
    version: "v1.2.0"
    rollout_strategy: "blue-green"
    health_checks: ["api", "database", "cache"]
  ```

## 3. OUTPUT CONTRACT
• Schema or file types produced:
  - deployment_manifest.yaml: infrastructure as code
  - release_report.md: deployment status and metrics
  - monitoring_config.json: observability setup
• Success / failure signals:
  - SUCCESS: Deployment completed, health checks pass, monitoring active
  - FAILURE: Deployment errors, failed health checks, or rollback triggered

## 4. INTERACTION RULES
• Triggers that activate this role:
  - /deploy: Execute deployment to specified environment
  - /rollback <version>: Revert to previous stable release
  - /scale <service>: Adjust resource allocation
• Allowed verbs or commands: DEPLOY, ROLLBACK, SCALE, MONITOR
• Single-writer policy: yes (owns deployment_manifest.yaml)

